node.text: When @marcuslemonis asked me to take part in his #platingchange initiative to combat food insecurity AND help struggling restaurants in the process, I immediately knew the only answer in my book. My love of all things @honeyhi has only grown through the years, not just because of their incredible food but because of the women behind it. They’re remarkable examples of what it takes to live out a dream while never failing to put their staff and the community ahead of themselves. If you feel inclined, text PLATE to 707070 to donate a meal to those in need and check out @platingchange or @marcuslemonis’s profile to learn more about this remarkable program.

Hey y’all! If you missed my live convo during the #sharethemicnow - check this out. 💫

This moment in time is a unique one. It’s inviting us to examine our most deeply held values. Whether you’re just recognizing the mass injustices against black people or like me, you’ve been intimately aware of the struggle for freedom from systemic racism, if you’re a person who claims to value JUSTICE and EQUITY, this moment is ours. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
We have a choice about how we will persist moving forward. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Time tested values hold you accountable to who you said you want to be - especially when it’s not easy to be you anymore. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
💯In the coming days it’ll be easy to get back to “business as usual.” But, I URGE you to remember that “business as usual” means there are still black people suffering from police violence, structural inequity in housing (redlining), negative racial bias in company hiring & promotion practices, (check the data for your fav company, are there black voices throughout the org?), school- to- prison pipeline where black & brown kids are facing disproportionately harsher punishments and the inequity goes on. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
The bell has been rung and it is loud. ⁣⁣
The message is clear. ⁣⁣
Racism has and will continue to ravage our country if we let it. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
💫In this video I offer you a reflection to help you look inward in order to commit to long term actions.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
💫To my fellow BIPOC folks, what would you tell your younger self about how you’re still protecting their dreams and joy through this season? We must protect our joy.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
💫White folks, what would your younger self say about the person you’ve become? What will you tell them about your role in this fight?⁣⁣
⁣
💫The fight against injustice is a fight against complacency and apathy. We need people who will rise to the occasion of this moment. People to continuously say “YES, I will fight.” I will use my voice, my skills, and my resources to dismantle systems that are destroying our chance of collective liberation. ⁣⁣
⁣
What’s your purposeful protest? ⁣⁣ - @jovianzayne ⁣⁣
#sharethemicnow #onpurpose #BLM #breonnataylor #blacklivesmatter 🎥: @twopointoh of #listenTwoMe

I don’t think I will ever find the proper words to articulate how deep the well of my love is for you but I will keep searching. 
I am constantly in awe of all that you are and never more so then this past year that has seen you become the most remarkable Dad I ever could have imagined. 
Thank you for your patience, your presence, your passion and all of the possibilities that a life with you has unlocked. I relish every adventure with you and am endlessly dumbfound and grateful at the incredible luck that brought us together. 
In other words, I love you more than I could say. 🥰. Happiest Birthday, @taylordawesgoldsmith and cheers to your best year yet!!

node.text:
Recently, the impact of COVID-19  uncovered a critical need to lift up an untapped powerhouse - mothers. As of April 2021, nearly 50% of moms have left the workforce due to the pandemic. 
It’s time for some major changes — and this is your chance to become a part of the solution!

@gugu_guru is the company that helped guide me in choosing the right products when preparing for Gus’s arrival. Honestly- they were lifesavers…. And now they are now creating the first-ever marketplace powered by moms and they need our help. Their mission is focused on empowering the millions of moms displaced by the COVID-19 pandemic, as well as the moms who have chosen to stay at home to raise their children by offering them a way to monetize their expertise.

By contributing to Gugu Guru’s @iFundWomen campaign, you are joining a movement that will support moms when they need our support more than ever. In exchange for your support, Gugu Guru is offering a variety of rewards. You can also contribute without buying anything. No amount is too small — even $1 dollar goes a very long way! 
Link to support is in {my stories / GG's bio}.
